'''Black Flight''' was a group of [[BTL-S8 K-wing assault starfighter]]s serving within the [[24th Bombardment Squadron]] as part of the [[New Republic Fifth Fleet]]. In [[17 ABY/Legends|17 ABY]] they participated in the [[Black Fleet Crisis]].

At the start of the campaign, Black Flight was one of three component flights within the squadron, consisting of six K-wings, with one pilot and one gunner per ship. The flight leader was an officer known as [[Hodo]], who was considered a possible candidate for the vacant post of squadron commander.

After the debacle at [[Doornik-319]], Black Flight was reduced to three planes, as part of a reorganization in which the squadron was reordered into four flights. During the [[Battle of ILC-905]], the three K-wings of the restructured Black Flight, and their escorting formation of six [[E-7 E-wing multi-role starfighter|E-wing escort starfighters]], were initially held in reserve, but they were tasked to attack the [[Aramadia-class thrustship|''Aramadia''-class thrustship]] ''[[Rizaron]]'', which had crippled the gunship [[Vanguard (Warrior-class)|''Vanguard'']] and destroyed their own K-wing counterparts from [[Green Flight]].

An attack run by [[Black One/Legends|Black One]] and [[Black Two/Legends|Black Two]] successfully destroyed ''Rizaron'', but [[Laser/Legends|laser]] and [[Ion cannon/Legends|ion cannon]] fire from ''Rizaron'' had claimed [[Black Three/Legends|Black Three]] and at least one of the accompanying E-wings, and the attack came too late to save ''Vanguard'', which was eliminated by the thrustship's final missile broadside.

